<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Italy-Mafia     05-23 0137</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Italy-Mafia,0142</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Dead, One Wounded, in Mob Murders in Naples</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NAPLES, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two men armed with a pistol and a sawed-off
shotgun entered a meat warehouse and fatally shot two cousins in
what police said appeared to be a Mafia killing.
   The gunmen wounded another man as they fled on a motorcycle.
   Investigators believe Monday's attack was tied to fights between
drug traffickers.
   The victims, Giorgio Norcaro, 34, and Vincenzo Cocozza, 43, were
allegedly neighborhood ``bosses'' in the Camorra, one of Italy's
most powerful family-structured criminal organizations.
   Luigi de Simone, 29, shot in the arm and leg while riding a
moped outside the warehouse, said he probably was hit by mistake
but investigators did not rule out the possibility he was also a
target.
   He was in good condition at a Naples hospital.
</TEXT>
