<SECOND>PM-Actor Sued,0294</SECOND>
<HEAD>Owners Say Girl Used Fake ID to Get Into Club</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A teen-age girl whom Rob Lowe is accused of
seducing and filming in a pornographic videotape looked like an
adult and met the actor after getting into a nightclub with false
ID, an owner of the club says.
   Meanwhile, District Attorney Lewis Slaton said he will interview
Lowe before deciding whether to file criminal charges against the
star of such movies as ``About Last Night'' and ``St. Elmo's Fire.''
   Lowe, 24, is under investigation on possible charges of sexual
exploitation of a minor, centering on a segment of the tape in
which a lawsuit contends he directs the 16-year-old girl in a sex
scene with a 22-year-old woman.
   The actor frequented the Rio club last summer during the
Democratic National Convention, co-owner Mable Roubique said Monday.
   ``Rob Lowe was in our nightclub, along with hundreds of other
people,'' she said. ``The two girls were in the club, and he did
meet them here. They were customers in the club.''
   Ms. Roubique said the club screens patrons for proof they are
21, the legal drinking age, but the girl used ``very
legal-looking'' false identification.
   She said employees saw Lowe leave the club with the woman and
the girl on the Sunday night before the convention began.
   The 16-year-old's mother filed a lawsuit May 12 against Lowe,
seeking unspecified damages for the alleged seduction of her
daughter.
   The lawsuit remained under temporary seal Monday.
   Lowe was at the Cannes Film Festival in France when the lawsuit
was filed and has not commented on the allegations. Tim Wood,
Lowe's manager in Los Angeles, has not returned telephone calls
seeking comment.
