<FIRST>u w PM-NewZealandQuake 1stLd-Writethru a0520 05-23 0177</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-New Zealand Quake, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0520,160</SECOND>
<HEAD>Major Quake Strikes Islands Near New Zealand</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: CORRECTS overline to say Quake struck islands near New Zealand,
rather than New Zealand.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A severe earthquake struck the Macquarie
Islands near New Zealand early today, the U.S. Geological Survey
reported.
   The quake was measured at 8.2 on the Richter Scale and occurred
at 6:55 a.m. EDT, officials said.
   It was the strongest temblor this year anywhere in the world and
was centered about 850 miles southwest of Christchurch, according
to the survey. It was the strongest since one measuring 8.1 on
October 20, 1986, in the Kermadec Islands in ths Pacific.
   The survey said it had no immediate reports of injuries.
   The Richter scale is a measure of the strength of a quake, with
each increase of one whole number indicating 10 times more energy
released.
   A quake of 8 or more on the scale is considered a ``great''
earthquake capable of tremendous damage. By comparison, the San
Francisco earthquake of 1906 has been estimated at 8.3.
</TEXT>
