<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--PayrollRobbed     05-23 0117</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Payroll Robbed,0119</SECOND>
<HEAD>Norwegian Peacekeepers' Payroll Robbed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TYRE, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thieves stole $60,000 from the paymaster's
office of the Norwegian troops serving with the United Nations
peacekeeping forces in Lebanon, an officer said Tuesday.
   The robbery took place Sunday night at the headquarters of the
620-member Norwegian battalion in the southern village of Ibl
Al-Saqi, said the Norwegian officer, who spoke on condition of
anonymity.
   He refused to elaborate, except to say an investigation is under
way.
   The 5,800 United Nations troops, drawn from nine nations, have
been deployed in southern Lebanon since 1978. They occupy a six- to
10-mile strip that separates Israel's self-proclaimed buffer zone
from the predominantly Shiite sector of south Lebanon.
</TEXT>
