<FIRST>r a PM-PoliceStandoff     05-23 0180</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Police Standoff,0186</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Killed in Fiery End to Standoff</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CLEVELAND (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two brothers died today in a house fire
apparently set by firebombs tossed at officers during a seven-hour
standoff, police said.
   The men inside the house fired at least two shots at officers,
said Lt. Al Jezior, police spokesman. Police did not return fire,
but SWAT officers shot tear gas into the house in an attempt to
drive the men out, he said.
   Officers were called Monday night by neighbors who said they had
been threatened by someone with a weapon. Police spoke with one
brother through a bullhorn but were unable to contact the other,
Jezoir said.
   Police told radio station WGAR one of the brothers may have been
holding the other hostage.
   Jezoir said the blaze began after at least four firebombs were
thrown toward officers. The Fire Department had been standing by
because one of the men had threatened to set the house on fire, the
spokesman said.
   After the flames subsided, police found the men dead, apparently
of smoke inhalation, police said.
