<HEAD>Parachutist Didn't Look Before He Leaped</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eric Lillie's parachute opened perfectly
after he jumped off a construction crane on an 18-story office
building early Tuesday but his landing was rough _ two police
officers were waiting for him.
   ``The officers were just passing by when they saw this guy jump
off the building,'' said Sgt. Jeff Hanson. ``The only question was
whether he was wearing a parachute.''
   The officers cited the 23-year-old Santa Monica man for
