<TEXT>
   A new submarine-hunting surveillance ship will
be christened Wednesday in Washington state, the Navy said Tuesday.
   The ceremonies for the surveillance ship Bold will be held at
the Tacoma Boatbuilding shipyards in Tacoma, Wash., with Sen. Slade
Gorton, R-Wash., making the main speech.
   The Bold is a T-AGOS-class surveillance ship and will be the
second Navy ship to bear that name. The vessel is 224 feet long, 43
