sanctions on fishery products exported to the United States if
driftnet agreements have not been signed by June 29.
   Mosbacher has the authority to decide whether the agreements
satisfy the monitoring and enforcement provisions of the Driftnet
Act passed by Congress in 1987.
   Lawmakers from Alaska, Washington state and Oregon have called
the tentative treaty inadequate and asked that it be renegotiated.
Representatives of the Northwest fishing industry and
environmentalists also have been highly critical of the pact.
   Critics contend the draft treaty does not provide for enough
observers on Japanese vessels or enough patrols in the legal
driftnet zone to check on compliance.
   An estimated 700 to 1,000 fishing vessels frt Ord, Calif., and the
5th
Infantry Division at Fort Polk, La.
   The Bush administration ordered additional troops to Panama and
began withdrawing military dependents after Gen. Manuel Antonio
Noriega, Panama's strongman leader, staged and then declared void a
presidential election when it became clear his candidate had lost.
   Some of the opposition candidates were subsequently attacked
during political rallies.
   According to the defense sources, the U.S. Southern Command,
which is headquartered in Panama, has occasionally run
``show-the-flag convoys'' in the past.
   ``But these are not just routine convoys,'' one official said
Tuesday. ``We're stepping up our posture and more have been
scheduled.''
