<FIRST>r i AM-PR-PrisonRiot     05-23 0218</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-PR-Prison Riot,0225</SECOND>
<HEAD>Prison Riot Injures 40</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN JUAN, Puerto Rico (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prisoners rioted after refusing to
return to their cells for a roll call, leaving 30 inmates and 10
guards injured on Tuesday, an official said.
   Ivette del Valle, spokeswoman for the Puerto Rico Corrections
Department, said the two-hour riot at the Bayamon Regional Prison
began at 11:30 p.m. Monday in a wing reserved for 148 youths tried
and convicted as adults.
   She said the youths broke apart beds and toilets and used the
pieces to attack guards when told to return to their cells for a
midnight roll call. During the day the youths are allowed to lounge
in the aisles and courtyard.
   Ms. del Valle said said the guards finally forced the youths
back into their cells by 1:30 a.m. Tuesday.
   She said the 40 casualties suffered minor head and arm injuries,
and some were briefly hospitalized.
   ``Everything is under control and the inmates who received
medical attention are back in the penitentiary,'' Ms. del Valle
said.
   The youths earlier demanded an audience with a Corrections
Administration official to hear their complaints there were not
enough towels and bedsheets. Ms. del Valle said the agency was
considering their demands.
   In all, 1,072 prisoners are incarcerated at Bayamon, 15 miles
south of San Juan.
</TEXT>
