<FIRST>r f BC-Britain-Stocks     05-23 0167</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Stocks,0173</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Shares Lower at Midday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices were lower at midday Tuesday, as a
small amount of shares were bought by institutions at bargain
prices.
   Dealers said shares were knocked back from the outset on
interest rate fears and concern over the direction of the pound but
rebounded on what dealers termed cheap buying. Stability in the
currency market helped some buyers regain their nerve, some traders
said.
   ``There's not a lot of business around,'' said one British
equities salesman. ``Whatever shares were bought this morning was
out of a necessity to round out positions rather than true
commitment to invest in the market.''
   At about 12:15 p.m. in London, the Financial Times-Stock
Exchange 100-share index was off 6.6 points, or 0.3 percent, at
2,162.4, its best level for the day and well off its minimum of
2,151.0, a decline of 18 points.
   Volume came to 245.5 million shares at midday, compared with
345.5 million shares at the same time Monday.
</TEXT>
