<FIRST>r f PM-AmericaWest-Airports     05-23 0241</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-America West-Airports,0250</SECOND>
<HEAD>America West Gets Slots for NY, Washington Airports</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHOENIX (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   America West Airlines, awarded long-sought
landing slots at Washington National and New York's LaGuardia
airports, plans to begin one-stop service to those destinations
within 30 days.
   The Phoenix-based carrier on Monday was awarded enough slots by
the Federal Aviation Administration for two round trips daily to
LaGuardia and three to Washington National.
   The slots became available because they no longer are being used
by Eastern Airlines, which has been crippled by financial and labor
troubles.
   Landings and takeoffs at the two airports are limited by the
federal government because of safety and noise restrictions.
   Although the slots must be returned within seven days of the
government's asking, America West is optimistic that the government
will allocate some permanent slots from a pool of unused or
underused slots.
   America West has been seeking to buy Eastern's Northeast shuttle
in part to obtain landing rights at LaGuardia and Washington
National, but Monday's announcement will not affect the company's
offer, America West spokeswoman Daphne Decino said.
   ``We have been trying to get this community one-stop service
into those airports for a long time,'' said Peter Otradovec,
America West vice president of planning. ``We have every intention
of starting and operating the service as long as we can.''
   America West, which has hubs in Phoenix and Las Vegas, already
serves New York's John F. Kennedy International Airport and
Baltimore-Washington Airport.
</TEXT>
