<FIRST>u f BC-Transco-Hess     05-23 0188</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Transco-Hess,0197</SECOND>
<HEAD>Hess To Buy Offshore Fields</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Amerada Hess Corp. has agreed to buy most of
Transco Exploration Partners Ltd.'s offshore properties in the Gulf
of Mexico for $911 million in cash.
   The sale, announced on Monday, includes 41 gas fields and three
oil fields off Louisiana and Texas as well as shore-based support
facilities and a gas supply contract.
   Amerada Hess said the proved or probable reserves in the fields
are estimated at 518 billion cubic feet of natural gas and more
than 12 million barrels of oil. That is expected to increase the
company's total gas reserves by about 25 percent and oil holdings
by 6 percent.
   ``The acquisition ... provides the company with highly promising
exploration potential in areas close to existing production,''
Amerada Hess said in a statement.
   But Wall Street didn't share Amerada Hess' enthusiasm, with some
analysts saying the company paid a premium for the properties.
Amerada Hess closed down $1.37{ to $38.37{ a share in composite
trading Monday on the New York Stock Exchange.
   Transco Exploration Partners soared $3.75 to close at $9.50 on
the NYSE.
</TEXT>
