<FIRST>r f BC-BoeingOrder     05-23 0119</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Boeing Order,0124</SECOND>
<HEAD>Netherlands Airlines In $430 Million Order</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEATTLE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Transavia Airlines of the Netherlands has ordered
six 737-300s and two 757 jetliners in a deal worth about $430
million, The Boeing Co. announced Tuesday.
   Boeing said in a statement that the order makes Transavia the
26th airline to order the twin-engine 757 and boosts total orders
for the model to 559. Transavia also took options on two additional
757s.
   Transavia's 737-300s are for delivery starting in November 1991,
and its first 757 is to be delivered in the first half of 1993.
   The deal boosts total 737 orders to 2,527 planes and Boeing's
total orders for the year to 551 planes worth about $30.4 billion.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
